The paper focuses on optimizing data management for deep learning workloads on heterogeneous main memory systems. This involves addressing challenges related to memory profiling and efficient data migration. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Additionally, the paper leverages domain knowledge about deep learning and employs a custom approach for data management, which suggests a connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.AR (Hardware Architecture). The paper also presents results on performance improvement, indicating a possible connection to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
